<font color="#FF0000">VETERANS DAY 1996</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 11 21:49:37 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
&quot;From the Base Camp of the 25th Infantry Division in Cu Chi, Republic of Vietnam, this is Army Sergeant Karl Gutknecht reporting...&quot; 28 years ago and it is like yesterday.  To get some connection Randy Zirk and I ran in the Vietnam Memorial 10k in Washington D. C. Sunday.  Susan sewed a Tropic Lightning patch on my Asics running shirt--I went to Washington from Madison because I thought the event would be about then, or now but nothing at all was said about us as veterans, or the war, or the wall, or those that can not run or those of us that have been blessed and still can run. In my head I thought there would be men from the 25th at the race..  I remembered running in Cu Chi with Sergeant Uyeno and Richard Moss... We did not run for fitness...I wonder where they all are now...  But after the race where not one word was said about veterans or Vietnam, or the Wall, and the soup and fruit and juice, at the Wall as we walked back to the car we met up with very special Tropic Lightning men right at the Wall who were taking a toy tank memorial to one who had been killed, to the Wall in rememberance 28 years ago  .  The connection this weekend in Washington with them and with the Big Red One, Air Cav and many many others was powerful and profound.  I got back to work at my state job at 3 in the afternoon today (after the wings of the DC-9 tipped a last good bye just before the 1 p.m. ceremony at the Wall which I had to miss because of my state job because I had taken five hours leave) and my supervisor nastily accousted me and said &quot;Where have you been?&quot; I said I had filled out a leave slip, and she said &quot;Well, we have a thousand things on our mind...we need to know where you are&quot; Jesus, they just will never get it!!!28 years ago I made radio tapes and sent them to hometown stations--three minute tapes about life as a gun bunny and a grunt and a cook and a truck driver...  Randy was also in the Tropic Lightning and comes from up the road in Elroy, Wisconsin.  Being at the Wall again today was where I was, with friends, with men that understand, with buddies, with Randy. and with that Tank driver who was killed then and remembered today in a very special way by all of us in the 25th who just came together and now are again apart.<br>

<p><code>-- gutknks@wheel.datcp.state.wi.us  (Karl Gutknecht) </code><p>


